The paper deals with question answering tasks, which are typically studied in the natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) communities. The use of latent variable learning and EM algorithm also suggests a focus on probabilistic modeling, which is common in the NLP and ML subfields. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves developing a learning scheme, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The tasks involve information retrieval and numerical reasoning, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
